This project was about Natural Language Processing and the problem was to be able to correctly label the types of words in a file. To solve the problem, Hidden Markov Models 
(HMMs) were implemented in Python code. The Viterbi algorithm was implemented within the code and used to solve the problem. The final program was able to achieve around
85% accuracy for correct labels out of 91 different labels. The autograder was used to test the functionality of the program.
